1 SECTION 1. A new article to the Constitution of North Dakota is created and enacted as
2 follows:
3 Section 1. An individual may not be elected to the office of governor or lieutenant governor
4 more than twice. This provision does not prevent the lieutenant governor from succeeding to the
5 office of governor, nor does it prevent the secretary of state from acting as governor.
6 Section 2 . An individual may not be elected agriculture commissioner, attorney general ,
7 auditor, insurance commissioner, public service commissioner, secretary of state,
8 superintendent of public instruction, tax commissioner, or treasurer more than three times.
9 Section 3. Notwithstanding section 1 of article XV of the Constitution of North Dakota, an
10 individual may not be elected to the house of representatives more than three times, nor may
11 an individual be elected to the senate more than three times.
12 Section 4 . Any prior election as a member of the house of representatives, a member of the
13 senate , the office of governor, lieutenant governor, and a statewide elected office, may not be
14 counted agains t the election of an individual occurring before the 2018 general election. An
15 individual's service by the lieutenant governor in the individual's capacity as president of the
16 senate does not count toward the cumulative amount of time an individual may serve as a
17 member of the senate.
18 Section 5 . The provisions of this article are severable. If any provision is held to be invalid ,
19 either on its face or as applied, the application of the remaining provisions of this article are not
20 affected.
21 Section 6 . If a conflict exists between any provision of this article and any other provision o f
22 this constitution, the provisions of this article control.
23 SECTION 2. REPEAL. Sections 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 of article XV of the Constitution of North
24 Dakota are repealed.
25 SECTION 3. EFFECTIVE DATE. If approved by the electors, this measure becomes
26 effective on January 1, 2027.
